Text: "Jaipur the 1st planned city in the 18th century. The most important part was\
  \ food and then comes the beauty out there.\nWhenever i think of the food from jaipur\
  \ my mouth waters like anything. Talking about the beauty, the people out there\
  \ are so much caring about the forts and the historical monuments. They have been\
  \ maintaining it with so much love and care just like we take care of a small baby.\
  \ Jaipur is a stepping stone for travellers heading towards the dessert cities of\
  \ Jaiselmer and Jodhpur. The distinctly coloured buildings is an cherry on the cake.\
  \ Its  oftenly called as PINK CITY.  These buildings were originally painted to\
  \ imitate the red sandstone architecture of Mugham cities. \nVidhyadhar Bhattacharya\
